<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-05-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-05-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="945" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d945">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.00/1579.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                Minister</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-14"><hi rend="italic">May 14,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>To the Department it appears that either the first or third plan of
                            confirming the presidency of Diaz would accord with Martinez’s note of
                            November 5, 1910, to Dawson, and also the Assembly’s decree of December
                            31, 1910, electing Diaz Vice President. Make suitable expression of this
                            Government’s satisfaction with the Diaz Government’s assurance of its
                            desire to continue with the program.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
